<p>Before we dive in further, let=E2=80=99s explain some security concepts =
that will be relevant throughout this article:</p>



<ul class=3D"wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Hashing</strong> involves changing data into a deterministic st=
ring that can=E2=80=99t be turned back into its original form without emplo=
ying extensive resources.</li>



<li><strong>Salting</strong> refers to adding a random string of characters=
 to a piece of data prior to hashing to add an extra layer of protection an=
d guarantee a unique output.</li>



<li><strong>Time-to-live (TTL)</strong> counts the time until data becomes =
useless and needs to be refreshed or replaced.</li>
</ul>
</div>



<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"h-what-are-google-s-enhanced-conversio=
ns"><strong>What are Google=E2=80=99s Enhanced Conversions?</strong><a href=
=3D"https://piwik.pro/blog/google-enhanced-conversions-meta-advanced-matchi=
ng-analytics/#h-what-are-google-s-enhanced-conversions" class=3D"heading-an=
chor"></a></h2>



<p><a href=3D"https://support.google.com/google-ads/answer/9888656?hl=3Den"=
>Google=E2=80=99s Enhanced Conversions</a> are designed to improve the accu=
racy of conversion measurement by using hashed data from your website. Enha=
nced Conversions are part of the Google Privacy Sandbox initiative, which i=
s Google=E2=80=99s attempt at developing measures to support advertising wi=
thout relying on third-party cookies.<br><br>As part of Enhanced Conversion=
s, <strong>Google captures the data that prospects input on your website wh=
en filling out a form or completing a purchase. Examples of this data inclu=
de visitors=E2=80=99 names, phone numbers, and email addresses.</strong> Th=
e data is kept pseudo-anonymized with a hashing algorithm known as SHA-256.=
 Through hashing, identifying information is transformed into a character s=
tring.<br><br>Once the hashed data is sent to Google, it is matched with si=
gned-in Google accounts to attribute campaign conversions to ad events such=
 as clicks or views. The platform can then attribute conversions across dev=
ices and platforms so advertisers can build retargeting audiences.</p>



<div class=3D"wp-block-group blogpost-also-like-box has-grey-10-background-=
color has-background is-layout-constrained wp-container-core-group-is-layou=
t-f855abbf wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained" style=3D"padding-top:var(-=
-wp--preset--spacing--16);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--32);padd=
ing-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--16);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--sp=
acing--32)">
<p>Note that the hashed first-party data referred to here doesn=E2=80=99t f=
it the standard definition of <a href=3D"https://piwik.pro/glossary/first-p=
arty-data/">first-party data</a> =E2=80=93 instead, it is a concept created=
 by Google. Google collects the hashed first-party data via gtag and doesn=
=E2=80=99t give advertisers direct access to it.</p>
</div>



<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"what-is-metas-advanced-matching"><stro=
ng>What is Meta=E2=80=99s Advanced Matching?</strong><a href=3D"https://piw=
ik.pro/blog/google-enhanced-conversions-meta-advanced-matching-analytics/#w=
hat-is-metas-advanced-matching" class=3D"heading-anchor"></a></h2>



<p>Like Google=E2=80=99s solution, Meta=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://www.fa=
cebook.com/business/help/611774685654668?id=3D1205376682832142">Advanced Ma=
tching</a> leverages data from your site or app to enhance conversion track=
ing.&nbsp;<br><br>This feature is part of the Conversions API (CAPI), which=
 is Meta=E2=80=99s response to privacy updates like Apple=E2=80=99s iOS 14 =
changes and the introduction of the <a href=3D"https://piwik.pro/glossary/a=
pp-tracking-transparency-att/">App Tracking Transparency (ATT)</a> prompt. =
The Conversions API allows advertisers to send data directly from their ser=
vers to Meta, bypassing the browser=E2=80=99s privacy features.<br><br>Adva=
nced Matching enables a website that uses the Meta Pixel to automatically c=
ollect visitors=E2=80=99 data and match them with users on their platforms.=
 If you use a form on your website, the technology gathers form data like e=
mail addresses and phone numbers, hashes it, and then transfers it to Faceb=
ook or Instagram.&nbsp;</p>



<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"benefits-of-enhanced-conversions-and-a=
dvanced-matching"><strong>Benefits of Enhanced Conversions and Advanced Mat=
ching</strong><a href=3D"https://piwik.pro/blog/google-enhanced-conversions=
-meta-advanced-matching-analytics/#benefits-of-enhanced-conversions-and-adv=
anced-matching" class=3D"heading-anchor"></a></h2>



<p>The two technologies come with several advantages for businesses:</p>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"improved-conversion-tracking-accuracy"=
><strong>Improved conversion tracking accuracy</strong><a href=3D"https://p=
iwik.pro/blog/google-enhanced-conversions-meta-advanced-matching-analytics/=
#improved-conversion-tracking-accuracy" class=3D"heading-anchor"></a></h3>



<p>By using first-party data, these technologies offer a more precise way t=
o attribute conversions, even across different devices and platforms. This =
leads to better-informed marketing decisions and optimized ad spend=E2=80=
=8B.</p>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"enhanced-roi"><strong>Enhanced ROI</st=
rong><a href=3D"https://piwik.pro/blog/google-enhanced-conversions-meta-adv=
anced-matching-analytics/#enhanced-roi" class=3D"heading-anchor"></a></h3>



<p>With more accurate conversion tracking, businesses can better measure th=
e return on their advertising investments. This allows for more effective b=
udget allocation and improved campaign performance=E2=80=8B.&nbsp;</p>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"data-security"><strong>Data security</=
strong><a href=3D"https://piwik.pro/blog/google-enhanced-conversions-meta-a=
dvanced-matching-analytics/#data-security" class=3D"heading-anchor"></a></h=
3>



<p>Both Google and Facebook emphasize the privacy-safe nature of their solu=
tions. Enhanced Conversions and Advanced Matching use secure hashing techni=
ques like SHA-256 to anonymize <a href=3D"https://piwik.pro/glossary/person=
al-data/">personal data</a> before transmission, safeguarding the data whil=
e enabling detailed conversion tracking.&nbsp;</p>



<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"privacy-concerns"><strong>Privacy conc=
erns&nbsp;</strong><a href=3D"https://piwik.pro/blog/google-enhanced-conver=
sions-meta-advanced-matching-analytics/#privacy-concerns" class=3D"heading-=
anchor"></a></h2>



<p>Despite Google=E2=80=99s and Meta=E2=80=99s claims that their solutions =
are privacy-compliant, there have been serious concerns about the ethical i=
mplications of scraping and utilizing personal data for conversion tracking=
.&nbsp;<br><br>Many argue that while this approach can enhance ad targeting=
 and conversion tracking, it may compromise user privacy. The balance betwe=
en effective marketing and respecting user privacy is a critical issue that=
 needs to be addressed to maintain user trust and comply with privacy regul=
ations=E2=80=8B.<br><br>Here are some additional criticisms concerning priv=
acy:</p>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"potential-for-reidentification"><stron=
g>Potential for reidentification</strong><a href=3D"https://piwik.pro/blog/=
google-enhanced-conversions-meta-advanced-matching-analytics/#potential-for=
-reidentification" class=3D"heading-anchor"></a></h3>



<p>The Federal Trade Commission (FTC) has highlighted that <a href=3D"https=
://www.ftc.gov/policy/advocacy-research/tech-at-ftc/2024/07/no-hashing-stil=
l-doesnt-make-your-data-anonymous">hashing does not fully protect user anon=
ymity</a> and can still allow user identification. Hashing transforms data =
into a unique string of characters, which can still be reversed or matched =
with sufficient computational effort and supplemental data. Thus, hashing d=
oes not fully anonymize the data, and businesses must remain vigilant in th=
eir privacy practices=E2=80=8B. This undermines the privacy safeguards that=
 hashing is supposed to provide and raises concerns about how securely user=
 data is being handled and stored by Google=E2=80=8B and Meta.</p>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"gdpr-compliance"><strong>GDPR complian=
ce</strong><a href=3D"https://piwik.pro/blog/google-enhanced-conversions-me=
ta-advanced-matching-analytics/#gdpr-compliance" class=3D"heading-anchor"><=
/a></h3>



<p>There are also concerns about <a href=3D"https://piwik.pro/glossary/gdpr=
/">GDPR</a> compliance when using Google=E2=80=99s Enhanced Conversions and=
 Meta=E2=80=99s Advanced Matching. GDPR mandates that personal data be proc=
essed lawfully, fairly, and transparently. Businesses must ensure data mini=
mization =E2=80=93 collecting only what is necessary for the intended purpo=
se =E2=80=93 and that they only use the data for the specific purposes for =
which consent was given.&nbsp;<br><br>Privacy experts argue that Google=E2=
=80=99s and Meta=E2=80=99s practice of scraping form data and using it for =
ad conversion tracking may not fully align with these principles, particula=
rly if users are not adequately informed or do not have a straightforward w=
ay to opt out=E2=80=8B of tracking=E2=80=8B.<br><br>On top of that, even th=
ough the data is hashed, it does not eliminate the privacy risks associated=
 with collecting and processing personal data without explicit user consent=
. Under GDPR, businesses must obtain clear and explicit consent from users =
before collecting their data and be transparent about how this data will be=
 used=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B. Consequently, companies that are subject to the re=
levant privacy regulations and want to adopt these technologies must ensure=
 they obtain the necessary user consent.</p>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"implementation-challenges"><strong>Imp=
lementation challenges</strong><a href=3D"https://piwik.pro/blog/google-enh=
anced-conversions-meta-advanced-matching-analytics/#implementation-challeng=
es" class=3D"heading-anchor"></a></h3>



<p>Next to privacy concerns, Google=E2=80=99s and Meta=E2=80=99s technologi=
es may come with implementation challenges. More advanced configurations re=
quire technical knowledge. Additional expertise might also be required to c=
onfigure tags and manage data privacy settings. In practice, this rarely ha=
ppens as decisions are left to those with technical knowledge of how both p=
latforms work rather than privacy teams that should oversee the setup proce=
ss.&nbsp;</p>



<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"adding-a-salt-to-the-wound"><strong>Ad=
ding a salt to the wound</strong><a href=3D"https://piwik.pro/blog/google-e=
nhanced-conversions-meta-advanced-matching-analytics/#adding-a-salt-to-the-=
wound" class=3D"heading-anchor"></a></h2>



<p>A salt is a random value added to the data before hashing, meaning that =
even identical inputs produce different hashes. Adding a salt to the hash c=
ould enhance privacy by making it significantly more challenging to reident=
ify users. This approach mitigates the risk of attackers using precomputed =
tables to reverse-engineer the original data, thereby providing stronger pr=
otection against reidentification.&nbsp;<br><br>However, this added privacy=
 measure would lead to lost revenue for companies like Google and Meta. The=
 reason is that salting would disrupt their ability to effectively match ha=
shed data across different sessions and devices. Without consistent hashes,=
 it=E2=80=99s impossible to track user behavior accurately and attribute co=
nversions, which is critical for optimizing ad targeting and measuring camp=
aign performance. Consequently, the precision of ad targeting would decreas=
e, leading to less effective advertising strategies and reduced ad revenue =
for these platforms=E2=80=8B.</p>



<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"how-hashing-works-in-piwik-pro"><stron=
g>How hashing works in Piwik PRO</strong><a href=3D"https://piwik.pro/blog/=
google-enhanced-conversions-meta-advanced-matching-analytics/#how-hashing-w=
orks-in-piwik-pro" class=3D"heading-anchor"></a></h2>



<p>Google and Facebook operate an ad business, while Piwik PRO provides ana=
lytics. Hence we can=E2=80=99t directly compare their features. However, we=
=E2=80=99re still able to contrast their approaches to privacy.&nbsp;<br><b=
r>Unlike Google and Facebook, which store hashed emails or phone numbers, P=
iwik PRO temporarily only links events with one visitor session.&nbsp;<br><=
br>Google and Facebook use hashed data to track and reidentify users across=
 different platforms, such as websites and mobile apps. Meanwhile, at Piwik=
 PRO, temporary linking is utilized for pre-consent data tracking to ensure=
 user data cannot be reidentified across sessions.<br><br>Here=E2=80=99s ho=
w hashing works in Piwik PRO:</p>



<ol class=3D"wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Data protection:</strong> When users visit a site, their client=
 device characteristics are hashed and salted using secure techniques.&nbsp=
;</li>



<li><strong>Active session detection:</strong> Piwik PRO maintains a <a hre=
f=3D"https://help.piwik.pro/support/questions/what-are-sessions-and-how-are=
-they-counted/#session-hash">session hash</a>, which is a mechanism linking=
 the visitor and session in memory for up to 30 minutes from the last updat=
e.&nbsp;</li>



<li><strong>No reidentification:</strong> Unlike Google and Facebook, Piwik=
 PRO drops the link between the visitor and their session (usually after ar=
ound 30 minutes, which is the session hash=E2=80=99s time-to-live (TTL)). T=
his means that once the data has been processed =E2=80=93 for example, a vi=
sitor=E2=80=99s session has ended =E2=80=93 for its intended purpose =E2=80=
=93 such as <a href=3D"https://piwik.pro/blog/how-to-do-useful-analytics-wi=
thout-personal-data/">anonymized analytics</a> =E2=80=93 the session hash i=
s discarded, making reidentification of the user impossible.</li>



<li><strong>User consent:</strong> Before any data that could identify a us=
er across sessions is collected or processed, explicit consent is obtained =
from the user. This aligns with GDPR and other privacy regulations prioriti=
zing user control over personal data.</li>
</ol>



<p>This methodology ensures that Piwik PRO=E2=80=99s use of hashing adheres=
 to privacy best practices, offering a robust solution for businesses that =
need to track user interactions without compromising privacy.</p>



